---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const marketplaceUrl = "https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=hestami.janumicode";
---

<Base title="Case Study: Hestami AI Real Property OS" description="A detailed walkthrough of JanumiCode processing a complex, multi-domain real property platform from a single product description document.">

  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-header__label">Case Study &mdash; Whitepaper</span>
        <h2>Hestami AI Real Property OS<br />& Platform</h2>
        <p>A detailed walkthrough showing how JanumiCode's governed workflow processes a complex, multi-pillar product vision — three platforms, twelve business domains, thirty-plus entities — from a single product description document into a verified, traceable architecture.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Input -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-header__label">The Input</span>
        <h2>A product vision document</h2>
        <p>A single markdown document — 708 lines — describing an integrated real property platform spanning three product pillars, twelve business domains, five persona groups, a full technology stack, and a phased delivery strategy. This is the entire prompt given to JanumiCode.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="body-text" style="max-width: 800px;">
        This is exactly the kind of input that breaks conventional AI coding tools: too large for a single context window, too interconnected for naive decomposition, and too compliance-sensitive for unsupervised execution. Below, we visualize the scope of what JanumiCode is asked to process — then walk through how it does it, step by step.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Three Pillars -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-header__label">Three Product Pillars</span>
        <h2>One platform, three markets</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="pillars">
        <!-- Pillar 1 -->
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-card__header pillar-card__header--p1">
            <span class="pillar-card__phase">PHASE 1</span>
            <h3 class="pillar-card__title">Hestami Home<br />Real Property Assistant</h3>
            <span class="pillar-card__subtitle">AI-Assisted Property Owner Services</span>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-card__body">
            <div class="pillar-card__personas">
              <span class="pillar-persona">Homeowners</span>
              <span class="pillar-persona">Small Landlords</span>
              <span class="pillar-persona">Property Investors</span>
            </div>
            <div class="pillar-card__domains">
              <span class="pillar-card__domains-label">9 Business Domains</span>
              <div class="pillar-domain-list">
                <span class="pillar-domain">Property & Ownership</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Portfolio Management</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Owner Intent & Intake</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Service Call Lifecycle</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Document Management</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Staff Service Execution</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">External HOA Context</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Vendor Coordination</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Decision & Trust Ledger</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pillar-card__problem">
              <span class="pillar-card__problem-label">Core Problem</span>
              <p>Property owners waste time and incur risk finding reliable contractors, coordinating estimates, comparing inconsistent bids, and verifying licenses and insurance.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Pillar 2 -->
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-card__header pillar-card__header--p2">
            <span class="pillar-card__phase">PHASE 2</span>
            <h3 class="pillar-card__title">Hestami Service Provider<br />Field Services Management</h3>
            <span class="pillar-card__subtitle">Contractor Operations Platform</span>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-card__body">
            <div class="pillar-card__personas">
              <span class="pillar-persona">Contractors</span>
              <span class="pillar-persona">Technicians</span>
              <span class="pillar-persona">Dispatchers</span>
            </div>
            <div class="pillar-card__domains">
              <span class="pillar-card__domains-label">9 Business Domains</span>
              <div class="pillar-domain-list">
                <span class="pillar-domain">Identity & Licensing</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Workforce & Technicians</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Pricebook & Materials</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Job Lifecycle & Work Orders</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Dispatch & Scheduling</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Mobile Field Operations</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Estimates & Invoicing</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Inventory & Procurement</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Maintenance Contracts</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pillar-card__problem">
              <span class="pillar-card__problem-label">Modeled After</span>
              <p>ServiceTitan — the operating system for the trades. Scheduling, dispatch, mobile technician app, quoting, invoicing, job costing, and inventory.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Pillar 3 -->
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-card__header pillar-card__header--p3">
            <span class="pillar-card__phase">PHASE 3</span>
            <h3 class="pillar-card__title">Hestami Community<br />Association Management</h3>
            <span class="pillar-card__subtitle">HOA / CAM Governance Platform</span>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-card__body">
            <div class="pillar-card__personas">
              <span class="pillar-persona">Board Members</span>
              <span class="pillar-persona">Community Managers</span>
              <span class="pillar-persona">Residents</span>
            </div>
            <div class="pillar-card__domains">
              <span class="pillar-card__domains-label">11 Core Domains</span>
              <div class="pillar-domain-list">
                <span class="pillar-domain">Association & Property</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Accounting (GL, AR/AP)</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Work Orders & Vendors</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Violations</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">ARC Requests</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Governance & Meetings</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Communications</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Owner Portal</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Documents & Records</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Reserve Studies</span>
                <span class="pillar-domain">Compliance</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pillar-card__problem">
              <span class="pillar-card__problem-label">Modeled After</span>
              <p>Vantaca — AI-native community management platform. Action-item workflow engine, AI voice agents, automated AP/AR, board and homeowner portals.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Common Data Model — 12 Domains -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-header__label">Common Data Model</span>
        <h2>12 CDM domains spanning<br />all three pillars</h2>
        <p>The product description defines a shared logical domain model. Each domain includes primary entities and the relationships they form — the foundation that JanumiCode must decompose, model, and verify.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="cdm-grid">
        <div class="cdm-domain">
          <span class="cdm-domain__num">1</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__name">Association / Entity / Property Model</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__entities">Organization, Association, Property, Housing Unit, Common Area, Person, Ownership, Management Contract</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cdm-domain">
          <span class="cdm-domain__num">2</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__name">Accounting</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__entities">Chart of Accounts, GL, Journal Entries, Assessments, Payments, AP Invoices, Vendor W-9/1099, Bank Accounts</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cdm-domain">
          <span class="cdm-domain__num">3</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__name">Workflow Automation</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__entities">Task, Workflow Step, Trigger, SLA Timer, Notification, Approval</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cdm-domain">
          <span class="cdm-domain__num">4</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__name">Violations</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__entities">Violation, Evidence, Notice Sequence, Hearing, Fine</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cdm-domain">
          <span class="cdm-domain__num">5</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__name">ARC (Architectural Requests)</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__entities">ARC Request, Plans, Committee, Review Action, Condition, Permit</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cdm-domain">
          <span class="cdm-domain__num">6</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__name">Work Orders / Maintenance</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__entities">Work Order, Asset, Vendor, Bid, Schedule, Completion, Invoice</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cdm-domain">
          <span class="cdm-domain__num">7</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__name">Communications</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__entities">Mass Email, SMS, Announcement, Letter Template, Calendar Event, Meeting Notice</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cdm-domain">
          <span class="cdm-domain__num">8</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__name">Governance</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__entities">Board, Roles, Meeting, Agenda, Minutes, Vote, Resolution, Policy Doc</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cdm-domain">
          <span class="cdm-domain__num">9</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__name">Owner Portal / CRM</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__entities">User Account, Role, Request, Payment Preference, Document Access</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cdm-domain">
          <span class="cdm-domain__num">10</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__name">Documents & Records</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__entities">CC&Rs, Bylaws, Rules, Financial Reports, Contracts, Reserve Studies, Inspection Reports</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cdm-domain">
          <span class="cdm-domain__num">11</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__name">Reserve Studies</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__entities">Reserve Component, Life/Remaining Life, Replacement Cost, Funding Plan</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cdm-domain">
          <span class="cdm-domain__num">12</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__name">Compliance</span>
          <span class="cdm-domain__entities">Statutory Deadline, Notice Requirement, Voting Rule, Audit Requirement, Resale Packet</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Platform Architecture Diagram -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-header__label">Proposed Platform Architecture</span>
        <h2>The system JanumiCode<br />must decompose</h2>
        <p>The product description specifies a complete technology stack. This is the architecture that JanumiCode's governed workflow will verify, decompose into components, and sequence for implementation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="arch-diagram">
        <!-- Clients Layer -->
        <div class="arch-layer">
          <div class="arch-layer__label">CLIENTS</div>
          <div class="arch-layer__boxes">
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--client">
              <span class="arch-box__name">SvelteKit Web</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Admin, Staff, Owner, Manager, Board Portals</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--client">
              <span class="arch-box__name">iOS Native</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Homeowner + Technician Apps</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--client">
              <span class="arch-box__name">Android Native</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Homeowner + Technician Apps</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="arch-wire"></div>

        <!-- Edge / CDN Layer -->
        <div class="arch-layer">
          <div class="arch-layer__label">EDGE</div>
          <div class="arch-layer__boxes">
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--infra">
              <span class="arch-box__name">Cloudflare CDN</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Only public entry point &bull; TLS termination</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="arch-wire"></div>

        <!-- Proxy Layer -->
        <div class="arch-layer">
          <div class="arch-layer__label">PROXY</div>
          <div class="arch-layer__boxes">
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--infra">
              <span class="arch-box__name">Traefik</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Reverse proxy &bull; SNI routing &bull; Request forwarding</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="arch-wire"></div>

        <!-- API + Auth Layer -->
        <div class="arch-layer">
          <div class="arch-layer__label">API & AUTH</div>
          <div class="arch-layer__boxes">
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--service">
              <span class="arch-box__name">oRPC API Layer</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Zod type-safe &bull; OpenAPI gen &bull; SDK gen</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--service">
              <span class="arch-box__name">Better-Auth</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Authentication services</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--service">
              <span class="arch-box__name">Cerbos</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Policy-based authorization engine</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="arch-wire"></div>

        <!-- Backend Layer -->
        <div class="arch-layer">
          <div class="arch-layer__label">BACKEND</div>
          <div class="arch-layer__boxes">
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--service">
              <span class="arch-box__name">Node.js (Bun)</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">High-perf API execution runtime</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--service">
              <span class="arch-box__name">DBOS</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Durable, versioned workflows &bull; Idempotent state transitions</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="arch-wire"></div>

        <!-- Data Layer -->
        <div class="arch-layer">
          <div class="arch-layer__label">DATA</div>
          <div class="arch-layer__boxes">
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--data">
              <span class="arch-box__name">PostgreSQL</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Primary store &bull; RLS multi-tenant isolation</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--data">
              <span class="arch-box__name">SeaweedFS</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Object storage &bull; Media files</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="arch-wire"></div>

        <!-- Media Pipeline Layer -->
        <div class="arch-layer">
          <div class="arch-layer__label">MEDIA PIPELINE</div>
          <div class="arch-layer__boxes">
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--util">
              <span class="arch-box__name">tusd</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Resumable uploads</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--util">
              <span class="arch-box__name">ClamAV</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Malware scanning</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--util">
              <span class="arch-box__name">ffmpeg</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Video processing</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--util">
              <span class="arch-box__name">libvips</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Image derivatives</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--util">
              <span class="arch-box__name">ExifTool</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Metadata extraction</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="arch-wire"></div>

        <!-- Observability -->
        <div class="arch-layer">
          <div class="arch-layer__label">OBSERVABILITY</div>
          <div class="arch-layer__boxes">
            <div class="arch-box arch-box--infra">
              <span class="arch-box__name">OpenTelemetry</span>
              <span class="arch-box__detail">Traces, metrics, logs &bull; External collector TBD (SigNoz)</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Deployment -->
        <div class="arch-deploy">
          <span class="arch-deploy__label">DEPLOYMENT</span>
          <span class="arch-deploy__text">Docker Compose &bull; Ubuntu Linux VM &bull; Containerized services</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="body-text" style="margin-top: var(--space-2xl); max-width: 700px;">
        This is the full scope of what JanumiCode receives in a single prompt. Three product pillars, twelve shared domains, a concrete technology stack, persona definitions, user journey sketches, and a phased delivery strategy. Below, we walk through what JanumiCode's governed workflow does with it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!--  PHASE 1: INTAKE                               -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

  <section class="section" id="intake">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-header__label">Phase 1 &mdash; Intake</span>
        <h2>From product description to<br />structured plan</h2>
      </div>

      <!-- Sub-phase: ANALYZING -->
      <div class="whitepaper-step">
        <div class="whitepaper-step__label">
          <span class="step-diamond"></span>
          <span>SUB-PHASE: ANALYZING</span>
        </div>
        <div class="whitepaper-step__body">
          <p>The Technical Expert silently analyzes the product description, codebase context, and workspace structure. It classifies the input as a <strong>complex multi-domain product</strong> and selects <strong>Proposer-Validator mode</strong> (PRODUCT_REVIEW flow) rather than conversational discussion — the document is too structured for free-form dialogue.</p>
          <p>Classification result: 3 pillars detected, 12+ CDM domains, technology stack specified, phased delivery strategy present.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Governed Stream Mockup: Analyzing -->
        <div class="gs-mockup">
          <div class="gs-mockup__header">
            <span class="gs-mockup__dot gs-mockup__dot--green"></span>
            <span class="gs-mockup__title">Governed Stream</span>
            <span class="gs-mockup__phase">INTAKE &mdash; ANALYZING</span>
          </div>
          <div class="gs-mockup__body">
            <div class="gs-cmd-block">
              <div class="gs-cmd-block__header">
                <span class="gs-cmd-block__icon">&#9670;</span>
                <span class="gs-cmd-block__label">Technical Expert &mdash; Analysis</span>
                <span class="gs-cmd-block__badge gs-cmd-block__badge--cli">CLI</span>
                <span class="gs-cmd-block__badge gs-cmd-block__badge--review">Review</span>
                <span class="gs-cmd-block__time">08:12:03 AM</span>
              </div>
              <div class="gs-cmd-block__content">
                <div class="gs-output-line"><span class="gs-kw">Classification:</span> PRODUCT_OR_FEATURE (confidence: 0.94)</div>
                <div class="gs-output-line"><span class="gs-kw">Intake Mode:</span> PROPOSER_VALIDATOR</div>
                <div class="gs-output-line"><span class="gs-kw">Pillars Detected:</span> 3</div>
                <div class="gs-output-line">&nbsp;&nbsp;1. Hestami Home Real Property Assistant</div>
                <div class="gs-output-line">&nbsp;&nbsp;2. Hestami Service Provider Field Services Management</div>
                <div class="gs-output-line">&nbsp;&nbsp;3. Hestami Community Association Management</div>
                <div class="gs-output-line"><span class="gs-kw">CDM Domains:</span> 12 (Association, Accounting, Workflow, Violations, ARC, Work Orders, Communications, Governance, Owner Portal, Documents, Reserve Studies, Compliance)</div>
                <div class="gs-output-line"><span class="gs-kw">Tech Stack:</span> SvelteKit, Bun, PostgreSQL, DBOS, Cerbos, oRPC, Traefik</div>
              </div>
              <div class="gs-cmd-block__footer">
                <span class="gs-status gs-status--success">Completed (success)</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Sub-phase: PROPOSING_DOMAINS -->
      <div class="whitepaper-step">
        <div class="whitepaper-step__label">
          <span class="step-diamond"></span>
          <span>SUB-PHASE: PROPOSING_DOMAINS</span>
        </div>
        <div class="whitepaper-step__body">
          <p>The Domain Proposer generates business domains and personas. For the Hestami product, it identifies <strong>15 business domains</strong> across the three pillars — the 12 CDM domains from the document plus 3 cross-cutting domains (Platform Identity & Auth, Notification Services, AI/ML Services) inferred from the technology stack.</p>
          <p>Each domain is presented as an MMP Mirror Card. The user reviews each assumption:</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Governed Stream Mockup: MMP Mirror Cards -->
        <div class="gs-mockup">
          <div class="gs-mockup__header">
            <span class="gs-mockup__dot gs-mockup__dot--cyan"></span>
            <span class="gs-mockup__title">Governed Stream</span>
            <span class="gs-mockup__phase">INTAKE &mdash; PROPOSING_DOMAINS</span>
          </div>
          <div class="gs-mockup__body">
            <div class="gs-mmp-card">
              <div class="gs-mmp-card__header">
                <span class="gs-mmp-card__type">MIRROR</span>
                <span class="gs-mmp-card__title">Business Domain Proposals &mdash; Round 1 of 4</span>
              </div>
              <div class="gs-mmp-items">
                <div class="gs-mmp-item gs-mmp-item--accepted">
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__status">ACCEPTED</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__id">PV-DOM-1</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__text">Association / Entity / Property Model &mdash; Foundational structure for all association-bound operations</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__source">document-specified</span>
                </div>
                <div class="gs-mmp-item gs-mmp-item--accepted">
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__status">ACCEPTED</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__id">PV-DOM-2</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__text">Accounting &mdash; Auditable GL, assessments, AP/AR, 1099 compliance</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__source">document-specified</span>
                </div>
                <div class="gs-mmp-item gs-mmp-item--accepted">
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__status">ACCEPTED</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__id">PV-DOM-3</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__text">Workflow Automation &mdash; DBOS versioned workflows, SLA timers, approval chains</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__source">document-specified</span>
                </div>
                <div class="gs-mmp-item gs-mmp-item--rejected">
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__status">REJECTED</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__id">PV-DOM-13</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__text">AI/ML Services &mdash; Cross-cutting AI capabilities (document extraction, matching)</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__source">ai-proposed</span>
                </div>
                <div class="gs-mmp-item gs-mmp-item--edited">
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__status">EDITED</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__id">PV-DOM-14</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__text">Platform Identity & Auth &mdash; Better-Auth + Cerbos policy engine (was: "Generic Auth")</span>
                  <span class="gs-mmp-item__source">ai-proposed &rarr; edited</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="gs-mmp-card__footer">
                <span class="gs-mmp-card__count">14 accepted &bull; 1 rejected &bull; 1 edited &bull; 0 deferred</span>
                <span class="gs-btn">Submit Decisions</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="whitepaper-step__body">
          <p><strong>Key governance moment:</strong> The AI proposed "AI/ML Services" as a cross-cutting domain. The user <em>rejected</em> it — AI capabilities should be embedded within each domain, not a separate horizontal layer. This rejection propagates: no entities, workflows, or integrations will be generated for a standalone AI domain in subsequent rounds.</p>
          <p>The user also <em>edited</em> "Platform Identity & Auth" to specify the concrete technology choices (Better-Auth + Cerbos) rather than the AI's generic label. This edited text carries forward into architecture.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Sub-phase: PROPOSING_JOURNEYS -->
      <div class="whitepaper-step">
        <div class="whitepaper-step__label">
          <span class="step-diamond"></span>
          <span>SUB-PHASE: PROPOSING_JOURNEYS</span>
        </div>
